    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Blocks, strips, or pegs, usually made of wood, set into or onto construction, such as masonry or steel, to serve as surface into which nails may be driven. An example of use is to attach crown molding by nails.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
